description.narrative: National, regional and woreda capacity strengthened to develop evidence-based health strategies and costed plans to coordinate and mobilize resources, and monitor and evaluate progress towards universal health, focusing on the most disadvantaged areas, which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Health Systems Strengthening, Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020 improved and equitable coverage of quality health interventions for Newborns, Children, Adolescent girls and Women across the continuum of care at community and Primary Health Care (PHC) level

description.narrative: UNICEF leverages resources for child health by strategically advising on the Health Sector Transformation Plan 2 (HSTP 2), based on the UNICEF supported Ethiopia Demographic Health Survey 2019, Data use Apps in DHIS 2 and birth notification. UNICEF has helped expansion of community-based health insurance (CBHI) to protect marginalized families from catastrophic child health expenditure to achieve Universal Health Coverage. UNICEF has ensured integrated child health supply provision for enabling primary health care child health services. UNICEF is technically advising Government on the development of an evidenced-based Optimization of the Health Extension Program (OHEP) Roadmap. | Status:Met | As-of Date:30/06/2020
